SIMPLE: zymogen
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Zymogen
<hw>Zym"o*gen</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Zyme</ets> +
<ets>-gen</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <def>A mother
substance, or antecedent, of an enzyme or chemical ferment; -- applied
to such substances as, not being themselves actual ferments, may by
internal changes give rise to a ferment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The pancreas contains but little ready-made ferment, though there
is present in it a body, <qex>zymogen</qex>, which gives birth to the
ferment.</q> <rj><qau>Foster.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zymogene</ent>⟦br⟧
